    <note>Cai Ni [13649] He presented answers to policy questions that flattered Cai(1) Jing [1649] and was made jinshi #1. Later it was claimed that he was a member of Cai(1) Jing's lineage and that he was to be honored as a lineage uncle. Han(1) Cuiyan's [656] son-in-law [twice, sororate] has the same generational name as Yi(4) and his brother. Han Cuiyan's other son-in-law, Jian [3853], and Han(1) Zhongyan's [644] son-in-law, Cheng [17803], are probably related as well--Yi(4) was probably a younger member of this probable lineage; I am making them all lineage (third) cousins in a separate jia of this Cai lineage. CBD, 5, 3807-8.[Not yet checked. 未考。]</note>
